- Whether there were adequate warnings or instructions provided
- If alternative, safer designs existed

For example, in Clark's case, the court might consider that a design that prevented accidental discharge could have been more reasonable.

```java
// Pseudocode for determining unreasonably dangerous products
public class UnreasonablyDangerousProductEvaluator {
    public boolean isUnreasonablyDangerous(String productName, String[] risks) {
        if (containsRisks(risks, "accidental discharge")) {
            return true; // If the product has a high risk of accidental injury
        }
        return false;
    }

    private boolean containsRisks(String[] risks, String riskType) {
        for (String r : risks) {
            if (r.equals(riskType)) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
