#### Legal Definition of Embezzlement in California
Section 508 [of the California Penal Code] defines embezzlement as follows: "Every clerk, agent, or servant of any person who fraudulently appropriates to his own use, or secretes with a fraudulent intent to appropriate to his own use, any property of another which has come into his control or care by virtue of his employment * * * is guilty of embezzlement."

:C/Java Code for Embezzlement Class
```java
public class Embezzlement {
    private String perpetrator;
    private String propertyTaken;
    private boolean fraudulentIntent;

    public Embezzlement(String perpetrator, String propertyTaken, boolean fraudulentIntent) {
        this.perpetrator = perpetrator;
        this.propertyTaken = propertyTaken;
        this.fraudulentIntent = fraudulentIntent;
    }

    public boolean isEmbezzlement() {
        return fraudulentIntent && (propertyTaken.equals("money") || propertyTaken.equals("other assets"));
    }
}
```
:p How does the legal definition of embezzlement in California relate to Sisuphan's case?
??x
The legal definition of embezzlement requires that the perpetrator has a fraudulent intent and appropriates or secretes property that came into their control by virtue of employment. In Sisuphan's case, he took money from his dealership (property) with the intention of using it for his own purpose rather than to help the company as he claimed.
