#### Reasonable Expectation of Privacy
The Fourth Amendment protects against searches that violate a person’s reasonable expectation of privacy. This means that the individual must both expect privacy and society must consider this expectation legitimate.
:p What constitutes a "reasonable expectation of privacy"?
??x
A “reasonable expectation of privacy” exists if (1) the individual actually expects privacy, and (2) the person's expectation is one that society as a whole would consider legitimate. For example, private communications or personal belongings are typically protected under this principle.
