The main sources of contract law include the common law, which governs most contracts, but can be modified or replaced by statutory laws such as the Uniform Commercial Code (UCC), or by administrative agency regulations. For instance, contracts related to services, real estate, employment, and insurance are typically governed by common law unless specifically altered by UCC provisions.

