#### Measure of Damages for Breach by Contractor
When a contractor breaches the construction contract—either by failing to begin or stopping work—the measure of damages is the cost of completion. This includes compensation for any delay in performance.

:p What are the damages if a contractor stops working partway through a project?
??x
If a contractor stops working partway through a project, the measure of damages is the cost of completing the remaining work plus reasonable compensation for any delay caused by their breach.

Example: If it costs $150,000 to complete a construction project that was 60% done, and there are delays worth an additional $30,000, total damages would be $180,000.
