:p How are damages measured when goods fail to conform?
??x
Damages are generally calculated by determining the difference in value between the delivered non-conforming goods (as accepted) and their returned equivalent. If the purchase price was fully paid upfront and not adjusted for the return, the buyer retains the entire pre-paid amount.

For example:
```java
public class DamageCalculation {
    private double originalPrice;
    private double returnedValue;

    public double calculateDamages() {
        return originalPrice - returnedValue;
    }
}
