#### Breach of Warranty and Rejection

Background context: Under the UCC, a buyer can cancel the contract and recover the purchase price if they rightfully reject goods that do not conform to the contract. The rejection must be communicated within a reasonable time after delivery.

:p What is the remedy for non-conforming goods?
??x
The remedy for non-conforming goods under the UCC includes the right of the buyer to cancel the contract and recover the purchase price if they rightfully reject the goods. This rejection must be communicated to the seller within a reasonable time after the goods' delivery or tender.

For example, in code:
```java
public class BreachHandling {
    private boolean isRejected;
    private LocalDate notificationDate;

    public void rejectGoods() {
        this.isRejected = true;
        this.notificationDate = LocalDate.now();
    }

    public boolean canRecoverPrice() {
        return isRejected && notificationDate.isBefore(calculateReasonableTime());
    }
}

public class CalculateReasonableTime {
    private static LocalDate calculateReasonableTime() {
        // Logic to determine a reasonable time
        return LocalDate.now().minusDays(30);
    }
}
```
