#### Negotiable Instruments Payable on Demand or at Definite Time
Background context: A negotiable instrument must be payable on demand or at a definite time [UCC 3–104(a)(2)]. This requirement ensures that the value and obligations of the instrument can be clearly determined. For instance, instruments with words like "Payable at sight" or "Payable upon presentment" are considered payable on demand.
:p What does it mean for an instrument to be "payable on demand"?
??x
An instrument is "payable on demand" if it contains the words "Payable at sight" or "Payable upon presentment," indicating that payment can be made immediately when presented. This means the maker, drawee, or acceptor must pay upon demand.
