#### Arbitrary and Capricious Test
The arbitrary and capricious test is a judicial standard used by courts to evaluate whether an agency's decision was made reasonably, logically, and with due consideration of relevant factors. An action will be considered arbitrary or capricious if it lacks explanation, appears irrational, or shows disregard for relevant evidence.
:p In Manin v. National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB), was the NTSB’s refusal to consider Manin's argument about his lack of knowledge arbitrary or capricious?
??x
In Manin v. National Transportation Safety Board, the NTSB’s refusal to consider Manin's argument that he did not know he had to report convictions for minor misdemeanors was indeed arbitrary and capricious.
The decision to depart from its own established policy (considering an applicant's understanding of what information a question sought) without explanation or justification lacked rationality. This departure appeared to be unjustified and ignored relevant evidence, thus failing the arbitrary and capricious test.
```java
// Pseudocode for evaluating agency actions under arbitrary and capricious test
public class ArbitraryCapriciousTest {
    public void evaluateDecision(Agent agent, Decision decision) {
        if (agent.hasExplainablePolicy()) {
            // Check if there is a policy in place
            boolean hasPolicy = agent.hasPolicy();
            if (!hasPolicy) {
                // Evaluate based on established procedures and rationality
                if (decision.isRational() && !decision.hasExplanation()) {
                    // Decision appears irrational or lacks explanation
                    declareDecisionArbitraryAndCapricious();
                } else {
                    // Decision is considered valid
                    upholdDecision();
                }
            } else {
                // Policy exists, check adherence to it
                if (agent.adheresToPolicy(decision)) {
                    // Decision adheres to policy and is rational
                    upholdDecision();
                } else {
                    // Departure from policy without explanation
                    declareDecisionArbitraryAndCapricious();
                }
            }
        } else {
            // No policy, evaluate based on other criteria
            if (decision.isRational()) {
                // Decision is rational even without a policy
                upholdDecision();
            } else {
                // Decision appears irrational
                declareDecisionArbitraryAndCapricious();
            }
        }
    }

    private void declareDecisionArbitraryAndCapricious() {
        // Log or notify that the decision is arbitrary and capricious
    }

    private void upholdDecision() {
        // Log or notify that the decision stands as valid
    }
}
```
